storms are told in the words of the people who experienced the events firsthand, lending a sense of immediacy to each story. Disasters bring out the worst as well as the best in people. Siegel focuses on the bravest individuals, including harbor pilot Thomas Freeborn who drowned while attempting to save fifty passengers and crew of a ship foundering on the Jersey Shore, and Warwicke Greene, a fourteen-year-old schoolboy who rescued the injured “like the hero of an epic poem” after a train wreck in the Hackensack Meadows. These and many other stories of forgotten acts of courage in the face of danger will make Disaster! an unforgettable read.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aDisasterszNew JerseyvAnecdotes. 0aDisasterszNew JerseyxHistory. 0aNatural disasterszNew JerseyvAnecdotes. 0aNatural disasterszNew JerseyxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066615140uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081356460940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813564609423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813564609/original  a978-3-11-066615-1  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK